# =============================================================================
# ZYNC Desktop Application - Code Owners Configuration
# =============================================================================
#
# This CODEOWNERS file defines who is responsible for code in this repository.
# When a pull request modifies code owned by a team or individual, those owners
# are automatically requested for review.
#
# GitHub Documentation:
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# =============================================================================
# How Code Owners Works
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. When a PR is opened, GitHub checks which files are modified
# 2. For each file, it finds the matching pattern in this file (last match wins)
# 3. The owners defined for that pattern are automatically requested for review
# 4. PR cannot be merged until all required code owner reviews are approved
#
# Syntax:
# - Pattern matching uses gitignore-style glob patterns
# - Later patterns take precedence over earlier ones
# - Use @username or @org/team-name to specify owners
# - Email addresses can also be used
#
# =============================================================================
# Review Requirements
# =============================================================================
#
# - All PRs require at least one approval from a code owner
# - Security-sensitive files require approval from the security team
# - CI/CD changes require approval from the DevOps team
# - Documentation changes require approval from the docs team
#
# =============================================================================

